==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shaveling
<hw>Shave"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A man shaved;
hence, a monk, or other religious; -- used in contempt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am no longer a <qex>shaveling</qex> than while my frock is on my
back.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shaver</ent>⟦br⟧
